<section id="body">
<ol id="splitquestionList">

  <li>Who do you have to write to?
  <list class="answerList">
  <li><g id="t1">the editor of a newspaper</g></li>
  <li><g id="t2">a prospective employer</g></li>
  <li><g id="t3">a shop assistant</g></li>
  <li><g id="t4">an interviewer</g></li>
  </list></li>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <li>How well do you know the person youare writing to?
  <list class="answerList">
  <li><g id="t5">A.  You are friends.</g></li>
  <li><g id="t6">B.  You have only just met them.</g></li>
  <li><g id="t7">C.  You have never met them.</g></li>
  </list></li>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <li>What style of letter should you write?
  <list class="answerList">
  <li><g id="t8">A.  formal</g></li>
  <li><g id="t9">B.  informal</g></li>
  </list></li>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <li>What do you have to do in this letter?
  <list class="answerList">
  <li><g id="t10">A.  request information</g></li>
  <li><g id="t11">B.  explain a situation</g></li>
  <li><g id="t12">C.  make arrangements</g></li>
  <li><g id="t13">D.  make an application</g></li>
  <li><g id="t14">E.  request action</g></li>
  </list></li>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <li>How many points do you have tocover in this letter?
  <list class="answerList">
  <li><g id="t15">A.  one</g></li>
  <li><g id="t16">B.  two</g></li>
  <li><g id="t17">C.  three</g></li>
  <li><g id="t18">D.  four</g></li>
  <li><g id="t19">E.  five</g></li>
  </list></li>
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <li>Which of the following would it be appropriate to write about in this letter?
    <list class="answerList">
  <li><g id="t20">A.  where you saw the advertisement</g></li>
  <li><g id="t21">B.  your previous jobs in a similar field</g></li>
